results.name: Complete list of solutions to y^2 = x^3 + 297; sequence gives x values.
comment: For corresponding y values and examples see A134104.
The parameter -297 of the curve corresponds to A200218(1). a(9)=A200216(1). - _Artur Jasinski_, Nov 29 2011
mathematica: sol[x_] := Solve[y > 0 && x^3 - y^2 == -297, y, Integers];

Reap[For[x = 1, x < 10^5, x++, sx = sol[x]; If[sx != {}, xy = {x, y} /. sx[[1]]; Print[xy]; Sow[xy]]; sx = sol[-x]; If[sx != {}, xy = {-x, y} /. sx[[1]]; Print[xy]; Sow[xy]]]][[2, 1]][[All, 1]] // Sort (* _Jean-François Alcover_, Feb 07 2020 *)
program: (MAGMA) Sort([ p[1] : p in IntegralPoints(EllipticCurve([0, 297])) ]); /* adapted from A029728 */
(SageMath) [i[0] for i in EllipticCurve([0, 297]).integral_points()] # _Seiichi Manyama_, Aug 26 2019
